{
  "translations": [
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b3",
      "translation": "We recognise that we still have much to accomplish in this important area. We have also recently completed a review of our Environmental, Social and Governance strategy. I am confident that our"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b4",
      "translation": "five strategic focus areas: enhancing physical and mental wellbeing, green operations, sustainable investment, talent and culture, and effective governance, will help us achieve our aspiration to be a"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b5",
      "translation": "global leader in Environmental, Social and Governance."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b6",
      "translation": "Outlook"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b7",
      "translation": "In 2020, the COVID-19 pandemic was undoubtedly the largest-scale public health emergency in our living memory. Affected businesses and households"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b8",
      "translation": "received unprecedented public financial and monetary support, which helped mitigate some of the extreme financial impacts caused by the pandemic and accelerated the pace of recovery, which was particularly evident in"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b9",
      "translation": "countries with well-developed health policies and infrastructure. However, there were significant differences between countries, and in these challenging circumstances, Asia (excluding Japan) recorded"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b10",
      "translation": "the relatively strongest global GDP performance. Currently, the global economy is just beginning to emerge from a deep recession and is entering the early stages of improvement."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b11",
      "translation": ""
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b12",
      "translation": "Although the effects of the pandemic have not yet ended, we believe 2021 will be a transitional year and we remain cautiously optimistic. The market anticipates the rollout of"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b13",
      "translation": "vaccination programmes and new therapies to help reduce infection rates and severity of the disease, enabling healthcare systems to respond more effectively to the pandemic and reduce mortality rates. Although we"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b14",
      "translation": "do not expect travel and consumer behaviour to return to pre-pandemic levels in the short term, as consumer confidence recovers, the scope of recovery is expected to gradually"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b15",
      "translation": "expand from manufacturing-led industries to consumer and service sectors. This will be particularly evident in countries with younger populations."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b16",
      "translation": "I am confident about AIA's long-term prospects. Despite near-term uncertainties, the domestic factors driving demand remain strong, and Asia's key demographic trends continue to provide positive structural support for"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b17",
      "translation": "AIA's long-term business outlook. With rising incomes, low private insurance penetration, and limited social welfare coverage,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b18",
      "translation": "market demand for AIA's products will continue to grow. We will leverage our substantial competitive advantages and strong"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b19",
      "translation": "track record of growth to build a more sustainable future for our communities and create shared value for all stakeholders."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b20",
      "translation": "Lee Yuan Siong"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b21",
      "translation": "Group Chief Executive Officer and President"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b23",
      "translation": "Growth rates are presented on a constant exchange rate basis, which management believes provides a clearer picture of the underlying business performance year-on-year."
    }
  ]
}
